People were told to try a salt and vinegar mixture if they wanted to see their enemies. Mzansi has been divided since the beginning of the week because of this supernatural mixture. Even celebrities have added their contribution to this frenzy. Comedian The Funny Chef, real name Lebohang Tlokana, released a mock video earlier today sharing her experience after trying out the salt and vinegar combo. She said she woke-up around 3am and she was met by lots of noises coming from the kitchen. She then decided to go and check what could have been causing the noise. She said she found five little tokoloshes using the mixture on the potato chips they had made in her kitchen. She jokingly ask them to share the chips but they refused. Record labels, Ambitious Records and Mabala Noise also took part by poking fun at each other, SEE BELOW TWEETS: 